text: Stupart Island is one of the uninhabited Canadian arctic islands in Nunavut, Canada. It lies in the Arctic Ocean, south-east of Lougheed Island and west of Edmund Walker Island. It is part of the Findlay Group. ==External links== * Stupart Island in the Atlas of Canada - Toporama; Natural Resources Canada Category:Islands of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago Category:Islands of Qikiqtaaluk Region Category:Islands of the Queen Elizabeth Islands Category:Uninhabited islands of Qikiqtaaluk Region
